{
  "page": "Lucas Lothston (father of Manfryd)",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">It is unknown whether this character and <a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Lothston_(husband_of_Falena)\" title=\"Lucas Lothston (husband of Falena)\">Lucas Lothston (husband of Falena)</a> were the same person.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\"><img alt=\"House Lothston.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/50px-House_Lothston.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/75px-House_Lothston.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/100px-House_Lothston.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Lucas Lothston<br /><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> the Pander</span></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\"><img alt=\"House Lothston.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/50px-House_Lothston.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/75px-House_Lothston.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b3/House_Lothston.svg/100px-House_Lothston.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alias</th><td>\nThe Pander<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\">House Lothston</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Rivermen\" title=\"Rivermen\">Rivermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Lothston\" title=\"Manfryd Lothston\">Manfryd Lothston</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Lucas Lothston</b>, also known as <b>the Pander</b>, was a <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a> and head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\">House Lothston</a>. He is remembered for bad deeds and for fathering <a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Lothston\" title=\"Manfryd Lothston\">Manfryd Lothston</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lucas_Lothston_(father_of_Manfryd)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lucas_Lothston_(father_of_Manfryd)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>On the way to <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_of_Tarth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brienne of Tarth\">Brienne of Tarth</a> meets Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Illifer_the_Penniless\" title=\"Illifer the Penniless\">Illifer the Penniless</a>, who chastises her for using a <a href=\"/index.php/Shield\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shield\">shield</a> with the <a href=\"/index.php/Arms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Arms\">arms</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lothston\" title=\"House Lothston\">House Lothston</a>. Illifer speaks of the shameful deeds of those who wore the Lothston arms, including Lord Lucas the Pander,<sup id=\"cite_ref-pander_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pander-4\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> and his son <a href=\"/index.php/Manfryd_Lothston\" title=\"Manfryd Lothston\">Manfryd o' the Black Hood</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lucas_Lothston_(father_of_Manfryd)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-pander-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-pander_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">It is unclear whether <a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Lothston_(husband_of_Falena)\" title=\"Lucas Lothston (husband of Falena)\">Lucas Lothston</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Falena_Stokeworth\" title=\"Falena Stokeworth\">Falena Stokeworth</a>'s husband, is the same character as the Lucas Lothston called the Pander. However, a pander is a pimp,<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> which would be a logical aspersion after Falena and Lucas arranged for their daughter <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Lothston\" title=\"Jeyne Lothston\">Jeyne</a> to become the <a href=\"/index.php/Mistress\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mistress\">mistress</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>, and especially since it was rumored Falena was also Aegon's lover at the same time.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lucas_Lothston_(father_of_Manfryd)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_4\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 4\">Chapter 4</a>, Brienne I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/pander#Noun\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikt:pander\">Wiktionary: Pander</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_iv.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon IV.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"wikitable succession-box noprint\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto; font-size:small;clear:both;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>Unknown</b><div style=\"font-size:90%\">Last known title holder:</div><b><a href=\"/index.php/Lucas_Lothston_(husband_of_Falena)\" title=\"Lucas Lothston (husband of Falena)\">Lucas Lothston</a> </b>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b> <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Lord of Harrenhal\">Lord of Harrenhal</a> </b>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"1\"><b>Unknown</b><div style=\"font-size:90%\">Next known title holder:</div><b><a href=\"/index.php/Danelle_Lothston\" title=\"Danelle Lothston\">Danelle Lothston</a> </b>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403174522\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.083 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.268 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1032/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 12990/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 9358/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1460/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 13/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 1/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3176/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.170/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.61 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  255.709      1 -total\n 82.46%  210.858      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 81.73%  208.996      1 Template:Infobox\n 12.92%   33.041     12 Tem